m\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[European Film Award for Best Editor|Best Editor]]\n| Janus Billeskov Jansen, Anne \u00d8sterud\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[71st Golden Globe Awards|Golden Globe Awards]]<ref name=GGnom>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/awards/2014-golden-globes-nominee-list-1200948220/|title=Golden Globes Nominations: The Full List|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=11 January 2014|accessdate=10 March 2014}}</ref>\n| 12 January 2014\n| [[Golden Globe Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n| \n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| [[29th Independent Spirit Awards|Independent Spirit Awards]]\n| 1 March 2014\n| [[Independent Spirit Award for Best Foreign Film|Best Foreign Film]]\n| \n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[International Online Film Critics' Poll]]\n| 26 January 2015\n| Best Actor\n| Mads Mikkelsen\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[London Film Critics Circle Awards 2012|London Film Critics Circle Awards]]\n| 20 January 2013\n| [[London Film Critics Circle Award for Actor of the Year|Actor of the Year]]\n| Mads Mikkelsen\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[National Board of Review Awards 2013|National Board of Review Awards]]\n| 4 December 2013\n| Top Foreign Films\n| \n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Nordic Council Film Prize]]\n| 30 October 2013\n| Nordic Council Film Prize\n| Thomas Vinterberg\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Online Film Critics Society Awards 2013|Online Film Critics Society Awards]]\n| 16 December 2013\n| [[Online Film Critics Society Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n| Mads Mikkelsen\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"15\"| [[Robert Award]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.screendaily.com/news/the-hunt-sweeps-danish-robert-awards/5065834.article|title=The Hunt sweeps Danish Robert awards|accessdate=31 January 2014|date=27 January 2014}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"15\"| 27 January 2014\n| [[Robert Award for Best Danish Film|Best Danish Film]]\n| Thomas Vinterberg\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Robert Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n| Thomas Vinterberg\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Screenplay\n| Thomas Vinterberg,Tobias Lindholm\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Robert Award for Best Actor in a Leading Role|Best Actor]]\n| Mads Mikkelsen\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actor\n| Thomas Bo Larsen\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Best Supporting Actress\n| Susse Wold\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Anne Louise Hassing\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Cinematography\n| Charlotte Bruus Christensen\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Editor\n| Anne \u00d8sterud, Janus Billeskov Jansen\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Production Design\n| Torben Stig Nielsen\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Costume Design\n| Manon Rasmussen\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Make-Up\n| Bj\u00f8rg Serup\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Original Score\n| Nikolaj Egelund\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Sound\n| Kristian Eidnes Andersen, Thomas J\u00e6ger\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Audience Award - Best Drama\n| Thomas Vinterberg\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[St. Louis Gateway Film Critics Association Awards 2013|St. Louis Gateway Film Critics Association Awards]]\n| 16 December 2013\n| Best Foreign Language Film\n|\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[San Diego Film Critics Society|San Diego Film Critics Society Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sdfcs.org/san-diego-film-critics-select-top-films-for-2013/|title=San Diego Film Critics Select Top Films for 2013|accessdate=19 December 2013}}</ref>\n| 11 December 2013\n| [[San Diego Film Critics Society Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n| \n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Toronto Film Critics Association Awards|Toronto Film Critics Association]]<ref>{{cite news|title=TFCA Announces 2013 Awards|url=http://www.torontofilmcritics.com/|accessdate=22 December 2013|newspaper=Toronto Film Critics Association|date=16 December 2013}}</ref>\n| 16 December 2013\n| [[Toronto Film Critics Association Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n| \n| {{won|Runner-up}}\n|-\n| [[Vancouver International Film Festival]]\n| 12 October 2012\n| Rogers People\u2019s Choice Award\n| Thomas Vinterberg\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association Awards 2013|Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association Awards]]\n| 9 December 2013\n| [[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n| \n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Home media==\n[[Nordisk Film]] released it in Denmark on 10 January 2013.<ref name=\"tilcannes\" /> The film was released on DVD and Blu-ray on 7 May 2013.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 86th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[List of Danish submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[False allegation of child sexual abuse]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.magpictures.com/thehunt/}}\n* {{IMDb title|2106476|The Hunt}}\n* {{mojo title|hunt2013|The Hunt}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes|the_hunt_2013|The Hunt}}\n* {{metacritic film|the-hunt|The Hunt}}\n* {{DNFt|74245}}\n\n{{Thomas Vinterberg}}\n{{The Nordic Council Film Prize}}\n{{Bodil Award for Best Danish Film}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hunt, The}}\n[[Category:2012 films]]\n[[Category:Danish-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s independent films]]\n[[Category:Danish films]]\n[[Category:Danish drama films]]\n[[Category:Danish independent films]]\n[[Category:Films about bullying]]\n[[Category:Films about educators]]\n[[Category:Films about pedophilia]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Thomas Vinterberg]]\n[[Category:Films set in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Denmark]]\n[[Category:Danish Christmas films]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Tobias Lindholm]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAccolades:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Hunt_(2012_film)"}
{"title_page": "Nudity clause", "text_new": "A '''nudity clause''' is a paragraph or a section in a performer's legal contract that stipulates which parts, if any, of the performer's body are to be exposed during a theatrical, television, cinematic, or other type of production. The clause may stipulate that a performer will not be required to perform in the [[Nudity|nude]], or it may specify that a performer is not allowed to perform in the nude. Nevertheless, a character they play may appear to be nude by the use of a \"[[body double]]\" in place of the performer during a [[Nudity in film|nude scene]] or the use of a flesh-colored [[bodystocking]] or a pubic area-covering [[merkin]]. Sometimes a performer will refuse to accept a role which involves nudity.\n\nMost performing contracts stipulate which body parts may be used in the final product.<ref name=globe>{{cite web |url= https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/film/the-naked-truth-about-on-screen-nudity/article550548/ |title=The naked truth about on-screen nudity|first= Liam|last= Lacey|work=theglobeandmail.com |date=2 March 2012|accessdate=2 March 2012}}</ref> This may, for example, be the back above the waist, include the buttocks, breasts, pubic hair, etc. They may also specify which parts cannot be shown - such as hands, neck, profile, etc. There are strict union guidelines around on-set nudity, which requires actors to be told of any nude scenes well in advance and nudity waivers require directors to itemize exactly what will be shown and how.<ref name=globe/>\n\nAt times exposure of each body part is given a commercial value and open to negotiation.<ref name=globe /> In 2001, [[Halle Berry]] appeared in the film ''[[Swordfish (film)|Swordfish]]'', which featured her first nude scene.<ref name=\"Hyland\">Ian Hyland (September 2, 2001). [http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4161/is_20010902/ai_n14532259/ \"The Diary: Halle's bold glory\"]. ''Sunday Mirror''. Accessed 2009-07-05. [http://arquivo.pt/wayback/wayback/20091001093252/http%3A//findarticles%2Ecom/p/articles/mi_qn4161/is_20010902/ai_n14532259/ Archived copy] at the [[Portuguese Web Archive]] (October 1, 2009).</ref> At first, she refused to be filmed topless in a sunbathing scene, but she changed her mind when Warner Brothers raised her fee substantially.<ref>Hugh Davies (February 7, 2001). [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/1310430/Halle-Berry-earns-extra-357000-for-topless-scene.html \"Halle Berry earns extra \u00a3357,000 for topless scene\"]. ''The Telegraph''. Accessed 2008-04-29.</ref> The brief flash of her breasts reportedly added $500,000 to her fee.<ref>Christa D'Souza (December 31, 2001). [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/4727871/And-the-winner-is....html \"And the winner is...] ''The Telegraph''. Accessed 2010-08-16.</ref> Berry, however, denied this,<ref name=\"Hyland\"/> explaining that after turning down numerous roles that required nudity, she decided to make ''Swordfish'' because her husband, [[Eric Ben\u00e9t]], supported her and encouraged her to take risks.<ref name=\"ebony\">\"Halle's big year\". (November 2002) ''[[Ebony (magazine)|Ebony]]''.</ref>\n\n==Purpose==\n{{Original research|following paragraphs|date=October 2007}}\nEspecially when they are launching their careers, many female performers refuse roles that require them to perform nude, either for personal or professional reasons; companies such as Disney often go to great lengths to protect their performers' 'family friendly' image.  'No-nudity' clauses are relatively rare, in that an actress that is approached to perform such a role is usually at a stage in their career where a polite refusal is acceptable, and in most cases, body-doubles, body-stockings or other alternate options are available.{{fact|date=September 2015}}\n\n== Studio imposition ==\nSometimes it is the studios or production companies that insist that their actresses do not take part in nude scenes or other appearances. For example, to preserve her wholesome image, [[Annette Funicello]], who was under contract with [[Walt Disney]], was not allowed to be seen in a two-piece bathing suit or show her navel in the [[beach party film]]s of the 1960s for [[American International Pictures]]; though the prohibition was not always followed.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Myth of the Hidden Navel|url=http://www.beachpartymoviemusic.com/TheMythoftheHiddenNavel.html|accessdate=February 20, 2012|publisher=Beachpartymoviemusic.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103012357/http://www.beachpartymoviemusic.com/themythofthehiddennavel.html|archive-date=2014-01-03|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== For cartoon characters ==\nNo-nudity clauses have also forbidden cartoon characters from appearing nude. [[Pamela Anderson]], for example, who appeared nude many times in print and in films, informed [[Reuters]] that she insisted on a no-nudity clause for her cartoon alter ego in ''[[Stripperella]]'', the adult animated series created by [[Stan Lee]].<ref name=\"jambar\">{{cite news|last=Andrews|first=Mark|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120722105228/http://www.thejambar.com/news/anderson-hypocritical-with-no-nudity-clause-1.2572105|url=http://www.thejambar.com/news/anderson-hypocritical-with-no-nudity-clause-1.2572105|date=June 25, 2003|archivedate=July 22, 2012|title=Anderson hypocritical with no-nudity clause|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Nudity in film]]\n*[[Morals clause]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Nudity}}\n\n[[Category:Nudity in film]]\n[[Category:Film]]\n", "text_old": "A '''nudity clause''' is a paragraph or a section in a performer\u2019s legal contract that stipulates which parts, if any, of the performer's body are to be exposed during a theatrical, television, cinematic, or other type of production. The clause may stipulate that a performer will not be required to perform in the [[Nudity|nude]], or it may specify that a performer is not allowed to perform in the nude. Nevertheless, a character they play may appear to be nude by the use of a \"[[body double]]\" in place of the performer during a [[Nudity in film|nude scene]] or the use of a flesh-colored [[bodystocking]] or a pubic area-covering [[merkin]]. Sometimes a performer will refuse to accept a role which involves nudity.\n\nMost performing contracts stipulate which body parts may be used in the final product.<ref name=globe>{{cite web |url= https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/film/the-naked-truth-about-on-screen-nudity/article550548/ |title=The naked truth about on-screen nudity|first= Liam|last= Lacey|work=theglobeandmail.com |date=2 March 2012|accessdate=2 March 2012}}</ref> This may, for example, be the back above the waist, include the buttocks, breasts, pubic hair, etc. They may also specify which parts cannot be shown - such as hands, neck, profile, etc. There are strict union guidelines around on-set nudity, which requires actors to be told of any nude scenes well in advance and nudity waivers require directors to itemize exactly what will be shown and how.<ref name=globe/>\n\nAt times exposure of each body part is given a commercial value and open to negotiation.<ref name=globe /> In 2001, [[Halle Berry]] appeared in the film ''[[Swordfish (film)|Swordfish]]'', which featured her first nude scene.<ref name=\"Hyland\">Ian Hyland (September 2, 2001). [http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4161/is_20010902/ai_n14532259/ \"The Diary: Halle's bold glory\"]. ''Sunday Mirror''. Accessed 2009-07-05. [http://arquivo.pt/wayback/wayback/20091001093252/http%3A//findarticles%2Ecom/p/articles/mi_qn4161/is_20010902/ai_n14532259/ Archived copy] at the [[Portuguese Web Archive]] (October 1, 2009).</ref> At first, she refused to be filmed topless in a sunbathing scene, but she changed her mind when Warner Brothers raised her fee substantially.<ref>Hugh Davies (February 7, 2001). [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/1310430/Halle-Berry-earns-extra-357000-for-topless-scene.html \"Halle Berry earns extra \u00a3357,000 for topless scene\"]. ''The Telegraph''. Accessed 2008-04-29.</ref> The brief flash of her breasts reportedly added $500,000 to her fee.<ref>Christa D'Souza (December 31, 2001). [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/4727871/And-the-winner-is....html \"And the winner is...] ''The Telegraph''. Accessed 2010-08-16.</ref> Berry, however, denied this,<ref name=\"Hyland\"/> explaining that after turning down numerous roles that required nudity, she decided to make ''Swordfish'' because her husband, [[Eric Ben\u00e9t]], supported her and encouraged her to take risks.<ref name=\"ebony\">\"Halle's big year\". (November 2002) ''[[Ebony (magazine)|Ebony]]''.</ref>\n\n==Purpose==\n{{Original research|following paragraphs|date=October 2007}}\nEspecially when they are launching their careers, many female performers refuse roles that require them to perform nude, either for personal or professional reasons; companies such as Disney often go to great lengths to protect their performers' 'family friendly' image.  'No-nudity' clauses are relatively rare, in that an actress that is approached to perform such a role is usually at a stage in their career where a polite refusal is acceptable, and in most cases, body-doubles, body-stockings or other alternate options are available.{{fact|date=September 2015}}\n\n== Studio imposition ==\nSometimes it is the studios or production companies that insist that their actresses do not take part in nude scenes or other appearances. For example, to preserve her wholesome image, [[Annette Funicello]], who was under contract with [[Walt Disney]], was not allowed to be seen in a two-piece bathing suit or show her navel in the [[beach party film]]s of the 1960s for [[American International Pictures]]; though the prohibition was not always followed.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Myth of the Hidden Navel|url=http://www.beachpartymoviemusic.com/TheMythoftheHiddenNavel.html|accessdate=February 20, 2012|publisher=Beachpartymoviemusic.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140103012357/http://www.beachpartymoviemusic.com/themythofthehiddennavel.html|archive-date=2014-01-03|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== For cartoon characters ==\nNo-nudity clauses have also forbidden cartoon characters from appearing nude. [[Pamela Anderson]], for example, who appeared nude many times in print and in films, informed [[Reuters]] that she insisted on a no-nudity clause for her cartoon alter ego in ''[[Stripperella]]'', the adult animated series created by [[Stan Lee]].<ref name=\"jambar\">{{cite news|last=Andrews|first=Mark|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120722105228/http://www.thejambar.com/news/anderson-hypocritical-with-no-nudity-clause-1.2572105|url=http://www.thejambar.com/news/anderson-hypocritical-with-no-nudity-clause-1.2572105|date=June 25, 2003|archivedate=July 22, 2012|title=Anderson hypocritical with no-nudity clause|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Nudity in film]]\n*[[Morals clause]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Nudity}}\n\n[[Category:Nudity in film]]\n[[Category:Film]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nudity_clause"}
{"title_page": "Law of cotangents", "text_new": "[[File:Herontriangle1greek.svg|thumb|270px|right|A triangle, showing the \"incircle\" and the partitioning of the sides.  The angle bisectors meet at the [[incenter]], which is the center of the [[Incircle and excircles of a triangle|incircle]].]]\n[[File:Herontriangle2greek.svg|thumb|270px|right|By the above reasoning, all six parts are as shown.]]\n{{Trigonometry}}\nIn [[trigonometry]], the '''law of cotangents'''<ref>The Universal Encyclopaedia of Mathematics, Pan Reference Books, 1976, page 530. English version George Allen and Unwin, 1964. Translated from the German version Meyers Rechenduden, 1960.</ref> is a relationship among the lengths of the sides of a triangle and the cotangents of the halves of the three angles.\n\nJust as three quantities whose equality is expressed by the [[law of sines]] are equal to the diameter of the [[circumscribed circle]] of the triangle (or to its reciprocal, depending on how the law is expressed), so also the law of cotangents relates the radius of the [[inscribed circle]] of a [[triangle]] (the [[inradius]]) to its sides and angles.\n\n==Statement==\nUsing the usual notations for a triangle (see the figure at the upper right), where {{math|''a''}}, {{math|''b''}}, {{math|''c''}} are the lengths of the three sides, {{math|''A''}}, {{math|''B''}}, {{math|''C''}} are the vertices opposite those three respective sides, {{math|''\u03b1''}}, {{math|''\u03b2''}}, {{math|''\u03b3''}} are the corresponding angles at those vertices, {{math|''s''}} is the semi-perimeter, that is, {{math|''s'' {{=}} {{sfrac|''a'' + ''b'' + ''c''|2}}}}, and {{math|''r''}} is the radius of the inscribed circle, the law of [[trigonometric function|cotangent]]s states that\n:<math>\\frac{\\cot\\left(\\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}\\right)}{s-a} = \\frac{\\cot\\left(\\tfrac{\\beta}{2}\\right)}{s-b} = \\frac{\\cot\\left(\\tfrac{\\gamma}{2}\\right)}{s-c} = \\frac{1}{r}\\,</math>\n\nand furthermore that the inradius is given by\n:<math>r = \\sqrt{\\frac{(s-a)(s-b)(s-c)}{s}}\\,.</math>\n\n==Proof==\nIn the upper figure, the points of tangency of the incircle with the sides of the triangle break the perimeter into 6 segments, in 3 pairs. In each pair the segments are of equal length. For example, the 2 segments adjacent to vertex {{math|''A''}} are equal. If we pick one segment from each pair, their sum will be the semiperimeter {{math|''s''}}. An example of this is the segments shown in color in the figure. The two segments making up the red line add up to {{math|''a''}}, so the blue segment must be of length {{math|''s'' \u2212 ''a''}}. Obviously, the other five segments must also have lengths {{math|''s'' \u2212 ''a''}}, {{math|''s'' \u2212 ''b''}}, or {{math|''s'' \u2212 ''c''}}, as shown in the lower figure.\n\nBy inspection of the figure, using the definition of the cotangent function, we have\n:<math>\\cot\\left(\\frac{\\alpha}{2}\\right) =\\frac{s-a}{r}\\,</math>\nand similarly for the other two angles, proving the first assertion.\n\nFor the second one\u2014the inradius formula\u2014we start from the [[List of trigonometric identities#Tangents and cotangents of sums|general addition formula]]:\n: <math> \\cot (u+v+w) = \\frac{\\cot u +\\cot v +\\cot w - \\cot u \\cot v \\cot w }{1-\\cot u \\cot v - \\cot v \\cot w -\\cot w \\cot u}.</math>\n\nApplying to {{math|cot{{big|{{big|(}}}}{{sfrac|''\u03b1''|2}} + {{sfrac|''\u03b2''|2}} + {{sfrac|''\u03b3''|2}}{{big|{{big|)}}}} {{=}} cot {{sfrac|\u03c0|2}} {{=}} 0}}, we obtain:\n\n: <math>  \\cot\\left(\\frac{\\alpha}{2}\\right)  \\cot \\left(\\frac{\\beta}{2}\\right)  \\cot \\left(\\frac{\\gamma}{2}\\right) = \\cot\\left(\\frac{\\alpha}{2}\\right) + \\cot \\left(\\frac{\\beta}{2}\\right) + \\cot \\left(\\frac{\\gamma}{2}\\right). </math>\n(This is also the [[Proofs of trigonometric identities#Miscellaneous -- the triple cotangent identity|triple cotangent identity]])\n\nSubstituting the values obtained in the first part, we get:\n:<math> \\frac {(s-a)}r \\frac {(s-b)}r \\frac {(s-c)}r = \\frac {s-a}r + \\frac {s-b}r +\\frac {s-c}r =\\frac{3s-2s}r=\\frac{s}r.</math>\nMultiplying through by {{math|{{sfrac|''r''<sup>3</sup>|''s''}}}} gives the value of {{math|''r''<sup>2</sup>}}, proving the second assertion.\n\n==Some proofs using the law of cotangents==\nA number of other results can be derived from the law of cotangents.\n\n* [[Heron's formula]]. Note that the area of  triangle {{math|''ABC''}} is also divided into 6 smaller triangles, also in 3 pairs, with the triangles in each pair having the same area.  For example, the two triangles near vertex {{math|''A''}}, being right triangles of width {{math|''s'' \u2212 ''a''}} and height {{math|''r''}}, each have an area of {{math|{{sfrac|1|2}}''r''(''s'' \u2212 ''a'')}}.  So those two triangles together have an area of {{math|''r''(''s'' \u2212 ''a'')}}, and the area {{math|''S''}} of the whole triangle is therefore\n::<math>\n\\begin{align}\nS &= r(s-a) + r(s-b) + r(s-c) = r\\bigl(3s - (a+b+c)\\bigr) = r(3s - 2s) = rs \\\\[8pt]\n\\end{align}\n</math>\n\n:This gives the result\n::{{math|''S'' {{=}} {{sqrt|''s''(''s'' \u2212 ''a'')(''s'' \u2212 ''b'')(''s'' \u2212 ''c'')}}}}\n:as required.\n\n*[[Mollweide's formula|Mollweide's first formula]]. From the addition formula and the law of cotangents we have\n::<math>\\frac {\\sin \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}-\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) }{\\sin \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}+\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) } = \\frac {\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) -\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) }{\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) +\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) }=  \\frac {a-b}{2s-a-b}.</math>\n\n:This gives the result\n::<math>\\dfrac {a-b}{c}=\\dfrac {\\sin \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}-\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right)}{\\cos \\left( \\tfrac{\\gamma}{2} \\right) }</math>\n:as required.\n\n*[[Mollweide's formula|Mollweide's second formula]]. From the addition formula and the law of cotangents we have\n::<math>\n\\begin{align}\n& \\frac {\\cos\\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}-\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) }{\\cos\\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}+\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) } =\n\\frac {\\cot\\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) \\cot\\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) +1}{\\cot\\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) \\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) -1} \\\\[6pt]\n= {} & \\frac {\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) +\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) +2\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\gamma}{2} \\right) }{\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) +\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) } =\n\\frac {4s-a-b-2c}{2s-a-b}.\n\\end{align}\n</math> \n:Here, an extra step is required to transform a product into a sum, according to the sum/product formula.\n:This gives the result\n::<math>\\dfrac {b+a}{c} = \\dfrac{\\cos \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}-\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) }{\\sin \\left( \\tfrac{\\gamma}{2} \\right) }</math>\n:as required.\n\n*The [[law of tangents]] can also be derived from this {{harv|Silvester|2001|p=99}}.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Law of sines]]\n*[[Law of cosines]]\n*[[Law of tangents]]\n*[[Mollweide's formula]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=Geometry: Ancient and Modern\n|last=Silvester|first=John R. \n|publisher=Oxford University Press\n|year=2001\n|isbn=9780198508250\n|pages=313\n|ref=harv\n}}{{refend}}\n\n[[Category:Trigonometry]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Herontriangle1greek.svg|thumb|270px|right|A triangle, showing the \"incircle\" and the partitioning of the sides.  The angle bisectors meet at the [[incenter]], which is the center of the [[Incircle and excircles of a triangle|incircle]].]]\n[[File:Herontriangle2greek.svg|thumb|270px|right|By the above reasoning, all six parts are as shown.]]\n{{Trigonometry}}\nIn [[trigonometry]], the '''law of cotangents'''<ref>The Universal Encyclopaedia of Mathematics, Pan Reference Books, 1976, page 530. English version George Allen and Unwin, 1964. Translated from the German version Meyers Rechenduden, 1960.</ref> is a relationship among the lengths of the sides of a triangle and the cotangents of the halves of the three angles.\n\nJust as three quantities whose equality is expressed by the [[law of sines]] are equal to the diameter of the [[circumscribed circle]] of the triangle (or to its reciprocal, depending on how the law is expressed), so also the law of cotangents relates the radius of the [[inscribed circle]] of a [[triangle]] (the [[inradius]]) to its sides and angles.\n\n==Statement==\nUsing the usual notations for a triangle (see the figure at the upper right), where {{math|''a''}}, {{math|''b''}}, {{math|''c''}} are the lengths of the three sides, {{math|''A''}}, {{math|''B''}}, {{math|''C''}} are the vertices opposite those three respective sides, {{math|''\u03b1''}}, {{math|''\u03b2''}}, {{math|''\u03b3''}} are the corresponding angles at those vertices, {{math|''s''}} is the semi-perimeter, that is, {{math|''s'' {{=}} {{sfrac|''a'' + ''b'' + ''c''|2}}}}, and {{math|''r''}} is the radius of the inscribed circle, the law of [[trigonometric function|cotangent]]s states that\n:<math>\\frac{\\cot\\left(\\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}\\right)}{s-a} = \\frac{\\cot\\left(\\tfrac{\\beta}{2}\\right)}{s-b} = \\frac{\\cot\\left(\\tfrac{\\gamma}{2}\\right)}{s-c} = \\frac{1}{r}\\,</math>\n\nand furthermore that the inradius is given by\n:<math>r = \\sqrt{\\frac{(s-a)(s-b)(s-c)}{s}}\\,.</math>\n\n==Proof==\nIn the upper figure, the points of tangency of the incircle with the sides of the triangle break the perimeter into 6 segments, in 3 pairs. In each pair the segments are of equal length. For example, the 2 segments adjacent to vertex {{math|''A''}} are equal. If we pick one segment from each pair, their sum will be the semiperimeter {{math|''s''}}. An example of this is the segments shown in color in the figure. The two segments making up the red line add up to {{math|''a''}}, so the blue segment must be of length {{math|''s'' \u2212 ''a''}}. Obviously, the other five segments must also have lengths {{math|''s'' \u2212 ''a''}}, {{math|''s'' \u2212 ''b''}}, or {{math|''s'' \u2212 ''c''}}, as shown in the lower figure.\n\nBy inspection of the figure, using the definition of the cotangent function, we have\n:<math>\\cot\\left(\\frac{\\alpha}{2}\\right) =\\frac{s-a}{r}\\,</math>\nand similarly for the other two angles, proving the first assertion.\n\nFor the second one\u2014the inradius formula\u2014we start from the [[List of trigonometric identities#Tangents of sums|general addition formula]]:\n: <math> \\cot (u+v+w) = \\frac{\\cot u +\\cot v +\\cot w - \\cot u \\cot v \\cot w }{1-\\cot u \\cot v - \\cot v \\cot w -\\cot w \\cot u}.</math>\n\nApplying to {{math|cot{{big|{{big|(}}}}{{sfrac|''\u03b1''|2}} + {{sfrac|''\u03b2''|2}} + {{sfrac|''\u03b3''|2}}{{big|{{big|)}}}} {{=}} cot {{sfrac|\u03c0|2}} {{=}} 0}}, we obtain:\n\n: <math>  \\cot\\left(\\frac{\\alpha}{2}\\right)  \\cot \\left(\\frac{\\beta}{2}\\right)  \\cot \\left(\\frac{\\gamma}{2}\\right) = \\cot\\left(\\frac{\\alpha}{2}\\right) + \\cot \\left(\\frac{\\beta}{2}\\right) + \\cot \\left(\\frac{\\gamma}{2}\\right). </math>\n(This is also the [[Proofs of trigonometric identities#Miscellaneous -- the triple cotangent identity|triple cotangent identity]])\n\nSubstituting the values obtained in the first part, we get:\n:<math> \\frac {(s-a)}r \\frac {(s-b)}r \\frac {(s-c)}r = \\frac {s-a}r + \\frac {s-b}r +\\frac {s-c}r =\\frac{3s-2s}r=\\frac{s}r.</math>\nMultiplying through by {{math|{{sfrac|''r''<sup>3</sup>|''s''}}}} gives the value of {{math|''r''<sup>2</sup>}}, proving the second assertion.\n\n==Some proofs using the law of cotangents==\nA number of other results can be derived from the law of cotangents.\n\n* [[Heron's formula]]. Note that the area of  triangle {{math|''ABC''}} is also divided into 6 smaller triangles, also in 3 pairs, with the triangles in each pair having the same area.  For example, the two triangles near vertex {{math|''A''}}, being right triangles of width {{math|''s'' \u2212 ''a''}} and height {{math|''r''}}, each have an area of {{math|{{sfrac|1|2}}''r''(''s'' \u2212 ''a'')}}.  So those two triangles together have an area of {{math|''r''(''s'' \u2212 ''a'')}}, and the area {{math|''S''}} of the whole triangle is therefore\n::<math>\n\\begin{align}\nS &= r(s-a) + r(s-b) + r(s-c) = r\\bigl(3s - (a+b+c)\\bigr) = r(3s - 2s) = rs \\\\[8pt]\n\\end{align}\n</math>\n\n:This gives the result\n::{{math|''S'' {{=}} {{sqrt|''s''(''s'' \u2212 ''a'')(''s'' \u2212 ''b'')(''s'' \u2212 ''c'')}}}}\n:as required.\n\n*[[Mollweide's formula|Mollweide's first formula]]. From the addition formula and the law of cotangents we have\n::<math>\\frac {\\sin \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}-\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) }{\\sin \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}+\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) } = \\frac {\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) -\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) }{\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) +\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) }=  \\frac {a-b}{2s-a-b}.</math>\n\n:This gives the result\n::<math>\\dfrac {a-b}{c}=\\dfrac {\\sin \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}-\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right)}{\\cos \\left( \\tfrac{\\gamma}{2} \\right) }</math>\n:as required.\n\n*[[Mollweide's formula|Mollweide's second formula]]. From the addition formula and the law of cotangents we have\n::<math>\n\\begin{align}\n& \\frac {\\cos\\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}-\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) }{\\cos\\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}+\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) } =\n\\frac {\\cot\\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) \\cot\\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) +1}{\\cot\\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) \\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) -1} \\\\[6pt]\n= {} & \\frac {\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) +\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) +2\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\gamma}{2} \\right) }{\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2} \\right) +\\cot \\left( \\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) } =\n\\frac {4s-a-b-2c}{2s-a-b}.\n\\end{align}\n</math> \n:Here, an extra step is required to transform a product into a sum, according to the sum/product formula.\n:This gives the result\n::<math>\\dfrac {b+a}{c} = \\dfrac{\\cos \\left( \\tfrac{\\alpha}{2}-\\tfrac{\\beta}{2} \\right) }{\\sin \\left( \\tfrac{\\gamma}{2} \\right) }</math>\n:as required.\n\n*The [[law of tangents]] can also be derived from this {{harv|Silvester|2001|p=99}}.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Law of sines]]\n*[[Law of cosines]]\n*[[Law of tangents]]\n*[[Mollweide's formula]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite book\n|title=Geometry: Ancient and Modern\n|last=Silvester|first=John R. \n|publisher=Oxford University Press\n|year=2001\n|isbn=9780198508250\n|pages=313\n|ref=harv\n}}{{refend}}\n\n[[Category:Trigonometry]]\n", "name_user": "GreenKeeper17", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eProof:fixed link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_of_cotangents"}
{"title_page": "Constantinople (book)", "text_new": "{{italictitle}}\n[[File:ConstantinopleCarolineTiltonEngtrans.pdf|thumb|page=13|1896 English translation by Caroline Tilton]]\n[[File:ConstantinoplebyAmicisLansdaletranslationMerrillBakered.pdf|thumb|page=12|1896 English translation, Volume I, by Maria Hornor Lansdale]]\n'''''Constantinople''''' ({{lang-it|'''Costantinopoli'''}}) is a non-fiction [[Travel literature|travelogue book]] by [[Edmondo de Amicis]] published in 1877 regarding [[Ottoman Constantinople|Constantinople]] in the [[Ottoman Empire]], now [[Istanbul]].\n\nAlberto Brambilla of [[Sorbonne University]] wrote that the book made Amicis \"one of the best-known Italian authors  abroad\".<ref name=Brambillap185>Brambilla, p. 185.</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe first edition was published in 1877.<ref name=SmithPD>{{cite web|author=Smith, PD|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2013/sep/06/constantinople-edmondo-de-amicis-review|title=Constantinople by Edmondo De Amicis \u2013 review |work=[[The Guardian]]|date=2013-09-06|accessdate=2020-03-31}}</ref> The original work had two volumes. [[Cesare Biseo]] illustrated an 1882 edition, and Brambilla wrote that this one \"will help shape the European imagination towards Istanbul,<!--Exact quote, so do NOT change to Constantinople--> and the Orient in general.\"<ref name=Brambillap185/> Multiple translations were derived from the Biseo version.<ref name=Brambillap185/>\n\nIn 2013 a new English translation by Stephen Parkin was released.<ref name=SmithPD/>\n\n==Reception==\n[[Orhan Pamuk]] gave a positive reception to the book and [[Umberto Eco]] himself used the guide when visiting Constantinople.<ref name=SmithPD/>\n\nPD Smith of ''[[The Guardian]]'' wrote that the book is \"A wonderfully eloquent account\".<ref name=SmithPD/>\n\nWilliam Armstrong in ''[[H\u00fcrriyet Daily News]]'' called it \"An [[orientalist]] bore\" with \"annoyingly [[purple prose]]\".<ref name=Armstrong>{{cite web|author=Armstrong, William|url=https://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/opinion/william-armstrong/an-orientalist-bore-70376|title=An orientalist bore|work=[[H\u00fcrriyet Daily News]]|accessdate=2020-03-31}}</ref> Armstrong stated \"it isn\u2019t clear what distinguishes De Amicis\u2019 memoir from the dozens of similar tomes written by intrepid Europeans at the time.\"<ref name=Armstrong/>\n\n==References==\n* {{cite web|author=Brambilla, Alberto|url=https://cdn.istanbul.edu.tr/file/1CD58DF90A/1D9A12DBFC9048FBBFC6C85698A54831?doi=10.26650/LITERA482712|title=\u201cThe fairy of a thousand lovers\u201d: Notes on Constantinople by Edmondo De Amicis|work=[[Litera: Journal of Language, Literature and Culture Studies]]|publisher=[[Istanbul University Press]]|year=2018|volume=28|issue=2|pages=185-200|doi=10.26650/LITERA48271}}\n\n===Notes===\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commonscat|Constantinople (book)}}\n* ''[https://archive.org/details/constantinople01amicgoog Constantinople]'', 1896 English translation by Caroline Tilton, also at [[Hathi Trust]] ([https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=hvd.32044013645478&view=1up&seq=21 Harvard U copy] and [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39015033152094&view=1up&seq=13 University of Michigan copy])\n* ''[https://archive.org/details/constantinople00amicgoog Constantinople Volume I]'', 1896 English translation by Maria Hornor Lansdale, [[Merrill and Baker]]. [https://archive.org/details/constantinople01lansgoog alternate printing by] [[Henry T. Coates & Co.]] - [http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/51728 Alternate links at] [[Project Gutenberg]]\n* ''[https://archive.org/details/constantinople00lansgoog Constantinople Volume II]'', 1896 English translation by Maria Hornor Lansdale, [[Henry T. Coates & Co.]] - [http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/52251 Alternate links at] [[Project Gutenberg]]\n[[Category:1877 books]]\n[[Category:Constantinople]]\n[[Category:Works about the Ottoman Empire]]\n[[Category:Travel books]]\n[[Category:Italian-language books]]\n{{turkey-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{italictitle}}\n[[File:ConstantinopleCarolineTiltonEngtrans.pdf|thumb|page=13|1896 English translation by Caroline Tilton]]\n[[File:ConstantinoplebyAmicisLansdaletranslationMerrillBakered.pdf|thumb|page=12|1896 English translation, Volume I, by Maria Hornor Lansdale]]\n'''''Constantinople''''' ({{lang-it|'''Costantinopoli'''}}) is a non-fiction [[Travel literature|travelogue book]] by [[Edmondo de Amicis]] published in 1877 regarding [[Ottoman Constantinople|Constantinople]] in the [[Ottoman Empire]], now [[Istanbul]].\n\nAlberto Brambilla of [[Sorbonne University]] wrote that the book made Amicis \"one of the best-known Italian authors  abroad\".<ref name=Brambillap185>Brambilla, p. 185.</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe first edition was published in 1877.<ref name=SmithPD>{{cite web|author=Smith, PD|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2013/sep/06/constantinople-edmondo-de-amicis-review|title=Constantinople by Edmondo De Amicis \u2013 review |work=[[The Guardian]]|date=2013-09-06|accessdate=2020-03-31}}</ref> The original work had two volumes. [[Cesare Biseo]] illustrated an 1882 edition, and Brambilla wrote that this one \"will help shape the European imagination towards Istanbul,<!--Exact quote, so do NOT change to Constantinople--> and the Orient in general.\"<ref name=Brambillap185/> Multiple translations were derived from the Biseo version.<ref name=Brambillap185/>\n\nIn 2013 a new translation by Stephen Parkin was released.<ref name=SmithPD/>\n\n==Reception==\n[[Orhan Pamuk]] gave a positive reception to the book and [[Umberto Eco]] himself used the guide when visiting Constantinople.<ref name=SmithPD/>\n\nPD Smith of ''[[The Guardian]]'' wrote that the book is \"A wonderfully eloquent account\".<ref name=SmithPD/>\n\nWilliam Armstrong in ''[[H\u00fcrriyet Daily News]]'' called it \"An [[orientalist]] bore\" with \"annoyingly [[purple prose]]\".<ref name=Armstrong>{{cite web|author=Armstrong, William|url=https://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/opinion/william-armstrong/an-orientalist-bore-70376|title=An orientalist bore|work=[[H\u00fcrriyet Daily News]]|accessdate=2020-03-31}}</ref> Armstrong stated \"it isn\u2019t clear what distinguishes De Amicis\u2019 memoir from the dozens of similar tomes written by intrepid Europeans at the time.\"<ref name=Armstrong/>\n\n==References==\n* {{cite web|author=Brambilla, Alberto|url=https://cdn.istanbul.edu.tr/file/1CD58DF90A/1D9A12DBFC9048FBBFC6C85698A54831?doi=10.26650/LITERA482712|title=\u201cThe fairy of a thousand lovers\u201d: Notes on Constantinople by Edmondo De Amicis|work=[[Litera: Journal of Language, Literature and Culture Studies]]|publisher=[[Istanbul University Press]]|year=2018|volume=28|issue=2|pages=185-200|doi=10.26650/LITERA48271}}\n\n===Notes===\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commonscat|Constantinople (book)}}\n* ''[https://archive.org/details/constantinople01amicgoog Constantinople]'', 1896 English translation by Caroline Tilton, also at [[Hathi Trust]] ([https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=hvd.32044013645478&view=1up&seq=21 Harvard U copy] and [https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39015033152094&view=1up&seq=13 University of Michigan copy])\n* ''[https://archive.org/details/constantinople00amicgoog Constantinople Volume I]'', 1896 English translation by Maria Hornor Lansdale, [[Merrill and Baker]]. [https://archive.org/details/constantinople01lansgoog alternate printing by] [[Henry T. Coates & Co.]] - [http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/51728 Alternate links at] [[Project Gutenberg]]\n* ''[https://archive.org/details/constantinople00lansgoog Constantinople Volume II]'', 1896 English translation by Maria Hornor Lansdale, [[Henry T. Coates & Co.]] - [http://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/52251 Alternate links at] [[Project Gutenberg]]\n[[Category:1877 books]]\n[[Category:Constantinople]]\n[[Category:Works about the Ottoman Empire]]\n[[Category:Travel books]]\n[[Category:Italian-language books]]\n{{turkey-stub}}\n", "name_user": "WhisperToMe", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eRelease", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantinople_(book)"}
{"title_page": "Peranbu", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 Indian Tamil-language film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Peranbu\n| image          = Peranbu poster.jpg\n| caption = Premiere poster\n| director       = [[Ram (director)|Ram]]\n| producer       = [[P. L. Thenappan]]\n| writer         = Ram\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Mammootty]]\n* Sadhana\n* [[Anjali (film actress)|Anjali]]\n* Anjali Ameer}}\n| music          = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cinematography = [[Theni Eswar (cinematographer) | Theni Eswar]]\n| editing        = [[Sathish Suriya]]\n| studio         = Shree Rajalakshmi Films\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2018|01|27|International Film Festival Rotterdam|2019|02|01|Worldwide|ref2=}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/mammootty-peranbu-release-date-5538276/|title=Mammootty's Peranbu gets a release date|date=14 January 2019|accessdate=23 January 2019|work=[[The Indian Express]]}}</ref>\n| runtime        = 147 minutes \n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| gross          = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n}}\n\n'''''Peranbu''''' ({{Translation|Compassion}}), titled ''Resurrection'' in English, is a 2019 Indian [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]]-language film written and directed by [[Ram (director)|Ram]] and produced by [[P. L. Thenappan]]. It features [[Mammootty]], Sadhana, [[Anjali (film actress)|Anjali]], and Anjali Ameer in the lead roles. The film's score and soundtrack are composed by [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]].  ''Peranbu'' premiered at the [[International Film Festival Rotterdam]] on 27 January 2018, and was later screened at the [[Shanghai International Film Festival]], [[China]] on 17 June.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/mammootty-tamil-film-peranbu-screened-at-international-film-festival-of-rotterdam-2018-1153864-2018-01-25|title=Mammootty's Tamil film Peranbu goes to International Film Festival Rotterdam 2018|date=25 January 2018|accessdate=27 January 2018|work=[[India Today]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://iffr.com/en/2018/films/resurrection|accessdate=27 January 2018|title=Resurrection|work=[[International Film Festival Rotterdam|IFFR]]|date=22 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"ap\">{{cite web|title=Peranbu screened at the Shanghai film festival|date=19 June 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|work=[[The Times of India]]|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/peranbu-screened-at-the-shanghai-film-festival/articleshow/64649810.cms}}</ref>\n\nThe film was also selected to be screened under the Indian Panorama category of 49th [[International Film Festival of India]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/mammootty-s-peranbu-be-screened-iffi-90865|title=Mammootty's 'Peranbu' to be screened at the IFFI|date=31 October 2018|accessdate=1 November 2018|author=Digital Native|work=[[The News Minute]]}}</ref> The film released in theatres on 1 February 2019, receiving positive reviews from critics.\n\n== Plot ==\nThe story of a single father Amudhavan and his daughter Pappa is told in chapters. \n\nAmudhavan works in [[Dubai]] while his wife Stella lives in India with their 14-year-old daughter Pappa who has a muscular health condition making her dependent to carry out daily functions. One day, Stella writes to Amudhavan asking him to take care of their daughter and leaves her family and runs away leading to Amu moving back home after 10 years to raise Pappa as a single father.  \n\nAmu finds it difficult to connect with Pappa having lived abroad for so long. They are shunned by their neighbours because of Pappa's health condition. They move in to his brother's house to live with his family and Amu's mother but his sister-in-law, irrationally fearing her own child will catch Pappa's \"illness\" asks them to move out. Amu returns home with Pappa where he continuously fights with some locals trying to force him to sell the house and leave the neighbourhood. Pappa and Amu slowly start bonding. One night when Pappa begins menstruation, Amu helps a panicked Pappa relax and seeks help from a woman named Vijaylakshmi. Vijaylakshmi (Viji) offers her help in return for basic needs and starts living with Amu and Pappa. Gradually, Viji and Amu become closer and marry. However, Viji's motives are revealed when she tries to kill Pappa by pushing her into a well only to be stopped by Amu. Amu discovers Viji is already married and was pretending to help them to gain ownership of his house. A dejected Amu leaves the house to Viji and moves away. Having received no money, he is forced to leave Pappa at home while he goes to work.\n\nPappa falls sick and the doctor diagnoses her with a fungal infection. She also refers Amu to Dr. Dhanapal who advises him to let Pappa stay at a special home for others with her health condition. Amu agrees with a heavy heart. On his way home he meets a trans-woman named Meera and they develop a bond. Meera helps him find a house. A few days later, while visiting Pappa, Amu discovers that Pappa was beaten by some workers at the home. He brings her back and seeks Dr. Dhanapal to understand more about Pappa's condition and her needs.\n\nFeeling helpless, Amu decides to end his and Pappa's lives and the two walk into the sea at night but are saved by Meera. The last chapter of Amuvadhan's story is about great love as he reveals that Meera taught him about love and the two are married. Pappa stays happily with her loving father and step-mother, Meera.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Mammooty]] as Amudhavan \"Amu\"\n* Sadhana as Pappa, Amudhavan and Stella's daughter\n*[[Anjali (film actress)|Anjali]] as Vijayalakshmi \"Viji\"\n* Anjali Ameer as Meera\n* [[Lizzie Antony]] as Thangam alias Stella, Amudhavan's wife\n* [[Samuthirakani]]  as Dr. Dhanapal\n* [[Vadivukkarasi]] as Amudhavan's mother\n* [[Livingston (actor)|Livingston]] as House owner\n* [[Aruldoss]] as Murugan, Amudhavan's friend and a taxi driver\n*  [[Pavel Navageethan]] as Babu\n* [[Shanmugarajan]] as Home in-charge\n* [[P. L. Thenappan]] as Land mafia member\n* G. R. Adithya as Amudhavan's brother\n* \"Poo\" Ram as David\n* Nitish Veera as Call, taxi driver\n* Arianna Romano as the Owner of the house\n{{colend}}\n\n;Malayalam version\n* [[Siddique (actor)|Siddique]]  as Dr. Dhanapal\n* [[Suraj Venjaramoodu]] as Murugan\n\n== Production ==\n[[Ram (director)|Ram]] developed the script with [[Mammootty]] in mind six years before he narrated it to the actor during early 2015.<ref name=\"r\">{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2016/nov/14/ram-finds-it-easy-to-act-in-a-film-than-directing-one-1538517.html|title=Ram finds it easy to act in a film than directing one|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|accessdate=1 March 2018|date=14 November 2016|author=S Subhakeerthana}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/director-ram-s-next-with-mammootty-news-tamil-pcvlnUjbhfedj.html |title=Director Ram's next with Mammootty |website=Sify.com |date=21 February 2015 |accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref> His regular composer [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] with cinematographer Theni Eeswar were confirmed from then.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.deccanchronicle.com/150526/entertainment-kollywood/article/ram\u2019s-next-film-different-love-story |date=27 May 2015|accessdate=|work=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|title=Ram's next film is a different love story? }}</ref> In July, Sadhana, the child artiste from his 2013 film ''[[Thanga Meengal]]'', was cast.<ref>{{cite web|author=Janani Karthik |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Anjali-does-a-special-role-in-Rams-Taramani/articleshow/48236975.cms |title=Anjali does a special role in Ram's Taramani|work=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com|date=27 July 2015|accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref> After [[P. L. Thenappan]] was signed on to produce the film under his banner Shree Raajalakshmi Films, and [[Anjali (film actress)|Anjali]] was cast for the female lead, Ram announced the title ''Peranbu'' in January 2016 beginning through a first look poster.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://m.indiatoday.in/story/peranbhu-director-ram-join-hands-with-mammootty-for-his-next/1/561281.html |date=3 January 2016|accessdate=22 December 2017|author= Indiatoday.in |work=[[India Today]]|title=Peranbhu: Director Ram joins hands with Mammootty for his next}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.ibtimes.co.in/mammootty-star-rams-tamil-movie-peranbu-anjali-661879 |date=4 January 2016|accessdate=22 December 2017|author=|work=[[International Business Times]]|title= Mammootty to star in Ram's Tamil movie Peranbu with Anjali}}</ref> Before filming, Ram stated that the film's theme is \"compassion\" and Mammootty plays a family man who \"rediscovers himself,\" while Sadhana plays his daughter, and Anjali the wife.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Compassion-is-the-theme-of-Rams-film-with-Mammootty/articleshow/50416951.cms|title=Compassion is the theme of Ram's film with Mammootty|author=Logesh Balachandran|date=5 January 2016|accessdate=12 March 2017|work=Times of India}}</ref> \n\n[[Principal photography]] commenced on 6 January 2016 in [[Kodaikanal]] and was planned to be shot in two schedules, with the next being in [[Chennai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Mammootty-begins-filming-his-Tamil-movie/articleshow/50510065.cms|title=Mammootty begins filming his Tamil movie|author=Sanjith Sidhardhan|date=9 January 2016|accessdate=1 May 2018|work=Times of India}}</ref> [[Mammootty]] and Sadhana's scenes were shot in January end.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.gulfnews.com/life-style/celebrity/desi-news/south-india/dubai-girl-stars-with-superstar-mammootty-1.1660784|title= Dubai girl stars with superstar Mammootty|work=[[Gulf News]]|author= Mythily Ramachandran|date=27 January 2016|accessdate=22 December 2017}}</ref> A lead role is portrayed by Anjali Ameer, a [[transsexual]] model from Kerala, in her [[feature film]] debut. For the role, the makers searched until 1 March 2016. She was selected with an audition, after Mammootty noticed a television report about her and suggested her name to Ram.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/Leisure/xryigGNyyYHV68xZfjro1M/Meet-Anjali-Ameer-Indias-first-transwoman-actor.html|title=Meet Anjali Ameer, India's first transwoman star|date=27 October 2017|accessdate=23 May 2018|author=Nidheesh M.K.|work=[[Livemint]]}}</ref><ref name=\"ah\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/from-a-boy-to-mammoottys-heroine/article17397222.ece|title=Meet Mammootty's new heroine|date=3 March 2017|author=P. K. Ajith Kumar|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=23 May 2018}}</ref> The second shooting schedule was held in and around Chennai from July to September.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Mammootty-to-play-an-Idukkikkaran-again-this-year/articleshow/53380185.cms|title=Mammootty to play an Idukkikkaran again this year|author=Anjana George|work=Times of India|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> In mid-2016, the team planned to make a [[Malayalam]] version of the film on Mammootty's suggestion.<ref name=\"r\" /><ref name=\"ml\">{{cite web|title=Mammootty's Tamil movie Peranbu is now bilingual|author=Deepika Jayaram|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Mammoottys-Tamil-movie-Peranbu-is-now-bilingual/articleshow/53366404.cms|accessdate=15 January 2018|work=Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Peranbu to be released in Malayalam|date=27 January 2017|first=Sanjith | last=Sidhardhan|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Peranbu-to-be-released-in-Malayalam/articleshow/55665393.cms|accessdate=4 September 2018|newspaper=The Times of India}} </ref> [[Suraj Venjaramoodu]] joined the new version playing Mammootty's friend.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Suraj-Venjaramoodu-plays-Mammoottys-aide-in-Peranbu/articleshow/53432992.cms|title=Suraj Venjaramoodu plays Mammootty's aide|author=Anjana George|accessdate=15 June 2018|date=28 July 2016|work=Times of India}} </ref> The dubbing and other post-production began from January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/170117/the-new-entrant-in-raams-peranbu.html|title=The new entrant in Raam's 'Peranbu'|work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |author=Janani K|date=17 January 2017|accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"ah\" /> By September, [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] composed all the songs and started working on the film score.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2017/sep/15/ram-not-doing-a-film-with-vikram-2149.html|title=Ram not doing a film with Vikram|author=S Subhakeerthana|date=15 September 2017|accessdate=15 July 2018|work=[[The New Indian Express]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/director-ram-s-peranbu-with-mammootty-is-ready-news-malayalam-rjvklccgiidfg.html|title=Director Ram's 'Peranbu' with Mammootty is ready|work=[[Sify]]|date=21 September 2017|accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Music ==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Peranbu\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{start date|2018|07|15|df=y}}\n| recorded   = 2017\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 16:24\n| language   = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label      = [[Saregama]] Tamil\n| producer   = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| prev_title = [[Raja Ranguski]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = [[Pyaar Prema Kaadhal]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack album and [[film score]] are composed by [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/mammootty-peranbu-audio-launch-5261698/|title=It took me 20 years to make a film with Mammootty: Ram at Peranbu audio launch|author=Ashameera Aiyappan|date=16 July 2018|accessdate=17 July 2018|work=[[Indian Express]]}}</ref> The audio was launched on 15 July 2018 at the [[Kalaivanar Arangam]] auditorium, Chennai. It received positive response.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/mollywood/yuvan-shankar-raja-gets-mass-response-at-mammoottys-peranbu-audio-launch-160501.htm|title=Yuvan Shankar Raja gets mass response at Mammootty's Peranbu audio launch|date=16 July 2018|author=LMK|work=[[In.com]]|accessdate=16 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/official-first-look-promo-mammootty-starrer-peranbu-out-84445|title=First-look promo of Mammootty-starrer 'Peranbu' out|date=9 July 2018|accessdate=15 July 2018|work=[[The News Minute]]}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column    = Singer(s)\n| total_length    = 16:24\n| headline = Track-List\n| title1 = Dhooramaai\n| extra1 = [[Vijay Yesudas]]\n| lyrics1 = [[Vairamuthu]]\n| length1 = 4:08\n| title2 = Anbe Anbin\n| extra2 =[[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]]\n| lyrics2 = [[Sumathy Ram]]\n| length2 =3:09\n| title3 = Vaanthooraal\n| extra3 = [[Sriram Parthasarathy]]\n| lyrics3 = [[Vairamuthu]]\n| length3 = 4:40\n| title4 = Setthu Pocchu Manasu\n| extra4 = [[Madhu Iyer]]\n| lyrics4 = [[Karunakaran]]\n| length4 =4:29\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe trailer and poster for worldwide release launched on 5 January 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/peranbu-trailer-mammootty-emotional-drama-video-5524866/|title=Peranbu trailer: Mammootty's intense emotional drama keeps the audience hooked|publisher=Indian Express|date=6 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=1Nk7bEYIA7c|title=Peranbu - Official Trailer -Mammootty - Ram -Yuvan Shankar Raja |publisher=Saregama Tamil on [[YouTube]]}}</ref> The film premiered at the 47th [[International Film Festival Rotterdam]], Netherlands on 27 January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iffr.com/en/audience-award-2018|title=Audience Award 2018|work=[[International Film Festival Rotterdam|IFFR]]|accessdate=1 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2018/may/17/peranbu-asian-premiere-in-shanghai-6063.html |title=Peranbu Asian premiere in Shanghai|author=CE Features|date=17 May 2018|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=[[The New Indian Express]]}}</ref> It was later screened at the 21st [[Shanghai International Film Festival]], China on 17 June 2018.<ref name=\"ap\" />\n\nIn January 2018, Ram stated that the film would have theatrical release in the summer of 2018 after its film festival premiers, but it was delayed. It is scheduled to release on 1 February 2019, in theatres worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2018/jan/02/peranbu--to-get-international-premiere-1742935.html|title=Peranbu to get international premiere|date=3 January 2018 |first1=Gopinath|last1= Rajendran|work=The New Indian Express|accessdate=27 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nThe film opened to positive responses from critics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/peranbu-sarvam-thaala-mayam-and-vantha-rajavathaan-varuven-movie-review-and-release-live-updates-5563880/|title=Sarvam Thaala Mayam, Peranbu and Vantha Rajavathaan Varuven movie review and release highlights|date=1 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/peranbu-movie-review-rating-by-audience-live-updates-791109|title=Peranbu movie review and rating by audience: Live updates|first=Shekhar H.|last=Hooli|date=1 February 2019|website=International Business Times, India Edition}}</ref> Karthik Kumar of ''Hindustan Times'' rated the film 4.5/5 and called the film \"a devastatingly beautiful intense emotional drama\" and was all praise about Ram's direction and performance by Mammootty and Sadhana. The critic also noted that ''Peranbu'' is Ram's \"quietest and most meditative and most rewarding film in years\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/peranbu-movie-review-mammootty-sadhana-starrer-is-a-devastatingly-beautiful-drama-about-father-daughter-bonding/story-RQ3BjQChlVm5bqkXJeftdL.html|title=Peranbu movie review: Mammootty, Sadhana starrer is a devastatingly beautiful drama about father-daughter bonding|date=1 February 2019|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref> Sowmya Rajendran of ''The News Minute'' rated the film 4/5 and wrote that \"the film that takes Tamil cinema to uncharted territories.\"<ref>[https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/peranbu-review-ram-s-father-daughter-tale-delicately-crafted-must-watch-film-96046 \"\u2018Peranbu\u2019 review: Ram\u2019s father-daughter tale is a delicately crafted must-watch film\"]</ref> Gautaman Bhaskaran rated the film 4/5 in his review for ''News 18'' and described the film as an \"extraordinarily sensitive portrayal of a father-daughter relationship.\" The critic however noted that the film \"could have been far more powerful if it had been shorter and tighter.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/peranbu-movie-review-mammootty-is-all-mellow-and-mature-in-this-father-daughter-drama-2022283.html|title=Peranbu Movie Review: Mammootty-Starrer is Bound to Stay With You for a Long Time|website=News18}}</ref> In his review for ''Film Companion'', [[Baradwaj Rangan]] rated the film 3.5/5 and called the film Ram's \"Least Angry, Most Moving Drama, and \"in terms of tone, the closest he\u2019s gotten to his guru, [[Balu Mahendra]].\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/peranbu-mammootty-ram-movie-review-mammootty-plays-the-gentlest-ram-hero-in-rams-least-angry-most-moving-drama/|title=Peranbu Movie Review: Mammootty Plays The Gentlest \"Ram Hero\" In Ram's Least Angry, Most Moving Drama|first=Baradwaj|last=Rangan|date=30 January 2019}}</ref> Padmakumar K. of ''Malayala Manorama'' described the film as \"a cinematic wonder that graces all aesthetics.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/2019/01/31/peranbu-mamootty-ram-sadhna-tamil-movie-review-rating.html|title=Mammootty's Peranbu review: A cinematic wonder that graces all aesthetics|website=OnManorama}}</ref> Rating the film 4/5, Haricharan Pudippedi from ''Firstpost'' called the film \"a devastatingly beautiful coming-of-age drama that is both poignant and equally depressing\" and appreciated Mammootty's role as one of his most matured performances.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/peranbu-movie-review-mammootty-gives-one-of-his-most-mature-performances-in-a-devastatingly-beautiful-film-5996511.html|title=Peranbu movie review: Mammootty gives one of his most mature performances in a devastatingly beautiful film- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=1 February 2019|website=Firstpost}}</ref> Rating the film as 'Good', film critic Veeyen affirmed that \"..brilliantly performed, visually striking and deftly structured, \u2018Peranbu\u2019 is an avowal of a fortune that we live with every day, and a prompt to remain forever thankful for the miracle called life.\" <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://veeyen.com/film-reviews/peranbu-2019-tamil-move-review-veeyen/|title=Peranbu (2019) Tamil Move Review - Veeyen|date=2 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|7738784}}\n\n{{Ram (director)}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:Transgender-related films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian drama films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 Indian Tamil-language film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Peranbu\n| image          = Peranbu poster.jpg\n| caption = Premiere poster\n| director       = [[Ram (director)|Ram]]\n| producer       = [[P. L. Thenappan]]\n| writer         = Ram\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Mammootty]]\n* Sadhana\n* [[Anjali (film actress)|Anjali]]\n* Anjali Ameer}}\n| music          = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cinematography = [[Theni Eswar (cinematographer) | Theni Eswar]]\n| editing        = [[Sathish Suriya]]\n| studio         = Shree Rajalakshmi Films\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2018|01|27|International Film Festival Rotterdam|2019|02|01|Worldwide|ref2=}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/mammootty-peranbu-release-date-5538276/|title=Mammootty's Peranbu gets a release date|date=14 January 2019|accessdate=23 January 2019|work=[[The Indian Express]]}}</ref>\n| runtime        = 147 minutes \n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| gross          = <!--Must be attributed to a reliable published source with an established reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb.-->\n}}\n\n'''''Peranbu''''' ({{Translation|Compassion}}), titled ''Resurrection'' in English, is a 2019 Indian [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]]-language film written and directed by [[Ram (director)|Ram]] and produced by [[P. L. Thenappan]]. It features [[Mammootty]], Sadhana, [[Anjali (film actress)|Anjali]], and Anjali Ameer in the lead roles. The film's score and soundtrack are composed by [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]].  ''Peranbu'' premiered at the [[International Film Festival Rotterdam]] on 27 January 2018, and was later screened at the [[Shanghai International Film Festival]], [[China]] on 17 June.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/mammootty-tamil-film-peranbu-screened-at-international-film-festival-of-rotterdam-2018-1153864-2018-01-25|title=Mammootty's Tamil film Peranbu goes to International Film Festival Rotterdam 2018|date=25 January 2018|accessdate=27 January 2018|work=[[India Today]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://iffr.com/en/2018/films/resurrection|accessdate=27 January 2018|title=Resurrection|work=[[International Film Festival Rotterdam|IFFR]]|date=22 December 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"ap\">{{cite web|title=Peranbu screened at the Shanghai film festival|date=19 June 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|work=[[The Times of India]]|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/peranbu-screened-at-the-shanghai-film-festival/articleshow/64649810.cms}}</ref>\n\nThe film was also selected to be screened under the Indian Panorama category of 49th [[International Film Festival of India]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/mammootty-s-peranbu-be-screened-iffi-90865|title=Mammootty's 'Peranbu' to be screened at the IFFI|date=31 October 2018|accessdate=1 November 2018|author=Digital Native|work=[[The News Minute]]}}</ref> The film released in theatres on 1 February 2019, receiving positive reviews from critics.\n\n== Plot ==\nThe story of a single father Amudhavan and his daughter Pappa is told in chapters. \n\nAmudhavan works in [[Dubai]] while his wife Stella lives in India with their 14-year old daughter Pappa who has a muscular health condition making her dependent to carry out daily functions. One day, Stella writes to Amudhavan asking him to take care of their daughter and leaves her family and runs away leading to Amu moving back home after 10 years to raise Pappa as a single father.  \n\nAmu finds it difficult to connect with Pappa having lived abroad for so long. They are shunned by their neighbours because of Pappa's health condition. They move in to his brother's house to live with his family and Amu's mother but his sister-in-law, irrationally fearing her own child will catch Pappa's \"illness\" asks them to move out. Amu returns home with Pappa where he continuously fights with some locals trying to force him to sell the house and leave the neighbourhood. Pappa and Amu slowly start bonding. One night when Pappa begins menstruation, Amu helps a panicked Pappa relax and seeks help from a woman named Vijaylakshmi. Vijaylakshmi (Viji) offers her help in return for basic needs and starts living with Amu and Pappa. Gradually, Viji and Amu become closer and marry. However, Viji's motives are revealed when she tries to kill Pappa by pushing her into a well only to be stopped by Amu. Amu discovers Viji is already married and was pretending to help them to gain ownership of his house. A dejected Amu leaves the house to Viji and moves away. Having received no money, he is forced to leave Pappa at home while he goes to work.\n\nPappa falls sick and the doctor diagnoses her with a fungal infection. She also refers Amu to Dr. Dhanapal who advises him to let Pappa stay at a special home for others with her health condition. Amu agrees with a heavy heart. On his way home he meets a trans-woman named Meera and they develop a bond. Meera helps him find a house. A few days later, while visiting Pappa, Amu discovers that Pappa was beaten by some workers at the home. He brings her back and seeks Dr. Dhanapal to understand more about Pappa's condition and her needs.\n\nFeeling helpless, Amu decides to end his and Pappa's lives and the two walk into the sea at night but are saved by Meera. The last chapter of Amuvadhan's story is about great love as he reveals that Meera taught him about love and the two are married. Pappa stays happily with her loving father and step-mother, Meera.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Mammooty]] as Amudhavan \"Amu\"\n* Sadhana as Pappa, Amudhavan and Stella's daughter\n*[[Anjali (film actress)|Anjali]] as Vijayalakshmi \"Viji\"\n* Anjali Ameer as Meera\n* [[Lizzie Antony]] as Thangam alias Stella, Amudhavan's wife\n* [[Samuthirakani]]  as Dr. Dhanapal\n* [[Vadivukkarasi]] as Amudhavan's mother\n* [[Livingston (actor)|Livingston]] as House owner\n* [[Aruldoss]] as Murugan, Amudhavan's friend and a taxi driver\n*  [[Pavel Navageethan]] as Babu\n* [[Shanmugarajan]] as Home in-charge\n* [[P. L. Thenappan]] as Land mafia member\n* G. R. Adithya as Amudhavan's brother\n* \"Poo\" Ram as David\n* Nitish Veera as Call, taxi driver\n* Arianna Romano as the Owner of the house\n{{colend}}\n\n;Malayalam version\n* [[Siddique (actor)|Siddique]]  as Dr. Dhanapal\n* [[Suraj Venjaramoodu]] as Murugan\n\n== Production ==\n[[Ram (director)|Ram]] developed the script with [[Mammootty]] in mind six years before he narrated it to the actor during early 2015.<ref name=\"r\">{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2016/nov/14/ram-finds-it-easy-to-act-in-a-film-than-directing-one-1538517.html|title=Ram finds it easy to act in a film than directing one|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|accessdate=1 March 2018|date=14 November 2016|author=S Subhakeerthana}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/director-ram-s-next-with-mammootty-news-tamil-pcvlnUjbhfedj.html |title=Director Ram's next with Mammootty |website=Sify.com |date=21 February 2015 |accessdate=4 April 2016}}</ref> His regular composer [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] with cinematographer Theni Eeswar were confirmed from then.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.deccanchronicle.com/150526/entertainment-kollywood/article/ram\u2019s-next-film-different-love-story |date=27 May 2015|accessdate=|work=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|title=Ram's next film is a different love story? }}</ref> In July, Sadhana, the child artiste from his 2013 film ''[[Thanga Meengal]]'', was cast.<ref>{{cite web|author=Janani Karthik |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Anjali-does-a-special-role-in-Rams-Taramani/articleshow/48236975.cms |title=Anjali does a special role in Ram's Taramani|work=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com|date=27 July 2015|accessdate=4 January 2016}}</ref> After [[P. L. Thenappan]] was signed on to produce the film under his banner Shree Raajalakshmi Films, and [[Anjali (film actress)|Anjali]] was cast for the female lead, Ram announced the title ''Peranbu'' in January 2016 beginning through a first look poster.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://m.indiatoday.in/story/peranbhu-director-ram-join-hands-with-mammootty-for-his-next/1/561281.html |date=3 January 2016|accessdate=22 December 2017|author= Indiatoday.in |work=[[India Today]]|title=Peranbhu: Director Ram joins hands with Mammootty for his next}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.ibtimes.co.in/mammootty-star-rams-tamil-movie-peranbu-anjali-661879 |date=4 January 2016|accessdate=22 December 2017|author=|work=[[International Business Times]]|title= Mammootty to star in Ram's Tamil movie Peranbu with Anjali}}</ref> Before filming, Ram stated that the film's theme is \"compassion\" and Mammootty plays a family man who \"rediscovers himself,\" while Sadhana plays his daughter, and Anjali the wife.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Compassion-is-the-theme-of-Rams-film-with-Mammootty/articleshow/50416951.cms|title=Compassion is the theme of Ram's film with Mammootty|author=Logesh Balachandran|date=5 January 2016|accessdate=12 March 2017|work=Times of India}}</ref> \n\n[[Principal photography]] commenced on 6 January 2016 in [[Kodaikanal]] and was planned to be shot in two schedules, with the next being in [[Chennai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Mammootty-begins-filming-his-Tamil-movie/articleshow/50510065.cms|title=Mammootty begins filming his Tamil movie|author=Sanjith Sidhardhan|date=9 January 2016|accessdate=1 May 2018|work=Times of India}}</ref> [[Mammootty]] and Sadhana's scenes were shot in January end.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.gulfnews.com/life-style/celebrity/desi-news/south-india/dubai-girl-stars-with-superstar-mammootty-1.1660784|title= Dubai girl stars with superstar Mammootty|work=[[Gulf News]]|author= Mythily Ramachandran|date=27 January 2016|accessdate=22 December 2017}}</ref> A lead role is portrayed by Anjali Ameer, a [[transsexual]] model from Kerala, in her [[feature film]] debut. For the role, the makers searched until 1 March 2016. She was selected with an audition, after Mammootty noticed a television report about her and suggested her name to Ram.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/Leisure/xryigGNyyYHV68xZfjro1M/Meet-Anjali-Ameer-Indias-first-transwoman-actor.html|title=Meet Anjali Ameer, India's first transwoman star|date=27 October 2017|accessdate=23 May 2018|author=Nidheesh M.K.|work=[[Livemint]]}}</ref><ref name=\"ah\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/from-a-boy-to-mammoottys-heroine/article17397222.ece|title=Meet Mammootty's new heroine|date=3 March 2017|author=P. K. Ajith Kumar|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=23 May 2018}}</ref> The second shooting schedule was held in and around Chennai from July to September.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Mammootty-to-play-an-Idukkikkaran-again-this-year/articleshow/53380185.cms|title=Mammootty to play an Idukkikkaran again this year|author=Anjana George|work=Times of India|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> In mid-2016, the team planned to make a [[Malayalam]] version of the film on Mammootty's suggestion.<ref name=\"r\" /><ref name=\"ml\">{{cite web|title=Mammootty's Tamil movie Peranbu is now bilingual|author=Deepika Jayaram|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Mammoottys-Tamil-movie-Peranbu-is-now-bilingual/articleshow/53366404.cms|accessdate=15 January 2018|work=Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Peranbu to be released in Malayalam|date=27 January 2017|first=Sanjith | last=Sidhardhan|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Peranbu-to-be-released-in-Malayalam/articleshow/55665393.cms|accessdate=4 September 2018|newspaper=The Times of India}} </ref> [[Suraj Venjaramoodu]] joined the new version playing Mammootty's friend.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/Suraj-Venjaramoodu-plays-Mammoottys-aide-in-Peranbu/articleshow/53432992.cms|title=Suraj Venjaramoodu plays Mammootty's aide|author=Anjana George|accessdate=15 June 2018|date=28 July 2016|work=Times of India}} </ref> The dubbing and other post-production began from January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/170117/the-new-entrant-in-raams-peranbu.html|title=The new entrant in Raam's 'Peranbu'|work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |author=Janani K|date=17 January 2017|accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"ah\" /> By September, [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]] composed all the songs and started working on the film score.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2017/sep/15/ram-not-doing-a-film-with-vikram-2149.html|title=Ram not doing a film with Vikram|author=S Subhakeerthana|date=15 September 2017|accessdate=15 July 2018|work=[[The New Indian Express]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/director-ram-s-peranbu-with-mammootty-is-ready-news-malayalam-rjvklccgiidfg.html|title=Director Ram's 'Peranbu' with Mammootty is ready|work=[[Sify]]|date=21 September 2017|accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Music ==\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Peranbu\n| type       = soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{start date|2018|07|15|df=y}}\n| recorded   = 2017\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 16:24\n| language   = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label      = [[Saregama]] Tamil\n| producer   = [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]]\n| prev_title = [[Raja Ranguski]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = [[Pyaar Prema Kaadhal]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack album and [[film score]] are composed by [[Yuvan Shankar Raja]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/mammootty-peranbu-audio-launch-5261698/|title=It took me 20 years to make a film with Mammootty: Ram at Peranbu audio launch|author=Ashameera Aiyappan|date=16 July 2018|accessdate=17 July 2018|work=[[Indian Express]]}}</ref> The audio was launched on 15 July 2018 at the [[Kalaivanar Arangam]] auditorium, Chennai. It received positive response.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.in.com/entertainment/mollywood/yuvan-shankar-raja-gets-mass-response-at-mammoottys-peranbu-audio-launch-160501.htm|title=Yuvan Shankar Raja gets mass response at Mammootty's Peranbu audio launch|date=16 July 2018|author=LMK|work=[[In.com]]|accessdate=16 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/official-first-look-promo-mammootty-starrer-peranbu-out-84445|title=First-look promo of Mammootty-starrer 'Peranbu' out|date=9 July 2018|accessdate=15 July 2018|work=[[The News Minute]]}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column    = Singer(s)\n| total_length    = 16:24\n| headline = Track-List\n| title1 = Dhooramaai\n| extra1 = [[Vijay Yesudas]]\n| lyrics1 = [[Vairamuthu]]\n| length1 = 4:08\n| title2 = Anbe Anbin\n| extra2 =[[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]]\n| lyrics2 = [[Sumathy Ram]]\n| length2 =3:09\n| title3 = Vaanthooraal\n| extra3 = [[Sriram Parthasarathy]]\n| lyrics3 = [[Vairamuthu]]\n| length3 = 4:40\n| title4 = Setthu Pocchu Manasu\n| extra4 = [[Madhu Iyer]]\n| lyrics4 = [[Karunakaran]]\n| length4 =4:29\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe trailer and poster for worldwide release launched on 5 January 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/peranbu-trailer-mammootty-emotional-drama-video-5524866/|title=Peranbu trailer: Mammootty's intense emotional drama keeps the audience hooked|publisher=Indian Express|date=6 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=1Nk7bEYIA7c|title=Peranbu - Official Trailer -Mammootty - Ram -Yuvan Shankar Raja |publisher=Saregama Tamil on [[YouTube]]}}</ref> The film premiered at the 47th [[International Film Festival Rotterdam]], Netherlands on 27 January 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://iffr.com/en/audience-award-2018|title=Audience Award 2018|work=[[International Film Festival Rotterdam|IFFR]]|accessdate=1 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2018/may/17/peranbu-asian-premiere-in-shanghai-6063.html |title=Peranbu Asian premiere in Shanghai|author=CE Features|date=17 May 2018|accessdate=18 May 2018|work=[[The New Indian Express]]}}</ref> It was later screened at the 21st [[Shanghai International Film Festival]], China on 17 June 2018.<ref name=\"ap\" />\n\nIn January 2018, Ram stated that the film would have theatrical release in the summer of 2018 after its film festival premiers, but it was delayed. It is scheduled to release on 1 February 2019, in theatres worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2018/jan/02/peranbu--to-get-international-premiere-1742935.html|title=Peranbu to get international premiere|date=3 January 2018 |first1=Gopinath|last1= Rajendran|work=The New Indian Express|accessdate=27 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nThe film opened to positive responses from critics.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/peranbu-sarvam-thaala-mayam-and-vantha-rajavathaan-varuven-movie-review-and-release-live-updates-5563880/|title=Sarvam Thaala Mayam, Peranbu and Vantha Rajavathaan Varuven movie review and release highlights|date=1 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/peranbu-movie-review-rating-by-audience-live-updates-791109|title=Peranbu movie review and rating by audience: Live updates|first=Shekhar H.|last=Hooli|date=1 February 2019|website=International Business Times, India Edition}}</ref> Karthik Kumar of ''Hindustan Times'' rated the film 4.5/5 and called the film \"a devastatingly beautiful intense emotional drama\" and was all praise about Ram's direction and performance by Mammootty and Sadhana. The critic also noted that ''Peranbu'' is Ram's \"quietest and most meditative and most rewarding film in years\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/peranbu-movie-review-mammootty-sadhana-starrer-is-a-devastatingly-beautiful-drama-about-father-daughter-bonding/story-RQ3BjQChlVm5bqkXJeftdL.html|title=Peranbu movie review: Mammootty, Sadhana starrer is a devastatingly beautiful drama about father-daughter bonding|date=1 February 2019|website=Hindustan Times}}</ref> Sowmya Rajendran of ''The News Minute'' rated the film 4/5 and wrote that \"the film that takes Tamil cinema to uncharted territories.\"<ref>[https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/peranbu-review-ram-s-father-daughter-tale-delicately-crafted-must-watch-film-96046 \"\u2018Peranbu\u2019 review: Ram\u2019s father-daughter tale is a delicately crafted must-watch film\"]</ref> Gautaman Bhaskaran rated the film 4/5 in his review for ''News 18'' and described the film as an \"extraordinarily sensitive portrayal of a father-daughter relationship.\" The critic however noted that the film \"could have been far more powerful if it had been shorter and tighter.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/peranbu-movie-review-mammootty-is-all-mellow-and-mature-in-this-father-daughter-drama-2022283.html|title=Peranbu Movie Review: Mammootty-Starrer is Bound to Stay With You for a Long Time|website=News18}}</ref> In his review for ''Film Companion'', [[Baradwaj Rangan]] rated the film 3.5/5 and called the film Ram's \"Least Angry, Most Moving Drama, and \"in terms of tone, the closest he\u2019s gotten to his guru, [[Balu Mahendra]].\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/peranbu-mammootty-ram-movie-review-mammootty-plays-the-gentlest-ram-hero-in-rams-least-angry-most-moving-drama/|title=Peranbu Movie Review: Mammootty Plays The Gentlest \"Ram Hero\" In Ram's Least Angry, Most Moving Drama|first=Baradwaj|last=Rangan|date=30 January 2019}}</ref> Padmakumar K. of ''Malayala Manorama'' described the film as \"a cinematic wonder that graces all aesthetics.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/2019/01/31/peranbu-mamootty-ram-sadhna-tamil-movie-review-rating.html|title=Mammootty's Peranbu review: A cinematic wonder that graces all aesthetics|website=OnManorama}}</ref> Rating the film 4/5, Haricharan Pudippedi from ''Firstpost'' called the film \"a devastatingly beautiful coming-of-age drama that is both poignant and equally depressing\" and appreciated Mammootty's role as one of his most matured performances.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/peranbu-movie-review-mammootty-gives-one-of-his-most-mature-performances-in-a-devastatingly-beautiful-film-5996511.html|title=Peranbu movie review: Mammootty gives one of his most mature performances in a devastatingly beautiful film- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=1 February 2019|website=Firstpost}}</ref> Rating the film as 'Good', film critic Veeyen affirmed that \"..brilliantly performed, visually striking and deftly structured, \u2018Peranbu\u2019 is an avowal of a fortune that we live with every day, and a prompt to remain forever thankful for the miracle called life.\" <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://veeyen.com/film-reviews/peranbu-2019-tamil-move-review-veeyen/|title=Peranbu (2019) Tamil Move Review - Veeyen|date=2 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|7738784}}\n\n{{Ram (director)}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:Transgender-related films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian drama films]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePlot:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 14-year old daughter \u2192 14-year-old daughter", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peranbu"}
{"title_page": "Maya 3D", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Maya 3D \n| image          = File:Maya3DPoster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = Donald Jayantha\n| producer       = Raja Sadesh Kumar <br> Srimathi Sadesh Kumar\n| writer         = Raja Sadesh Kumar\n| screenplay     = Pubudu Chathuranga \n| based on       = Tamil film ''[[Kanchana (2011 film)|Kanchana]]''\n| starring       = [[Ranjan Ramanayake]] <br> [[Pubudu Chathuranga]] <br> Shehara Hewadewa\n| music          = [[Bathiya and Santhush]]\n| cinematography = Ayeshmantha Hettiarachchi\n| editing        = Pravin Jayaratne\n| studio         = Real Image Creations\n| distributor    = EAP Film Circuit\n| released       = 14 September 2016\n| runtime        = \n| country        = Sri Lanka\n| language       = Sinhalese\n| gross          = 7 LKR Crores (in 31days)\n| italic title   = \n| budget         = \n| film_name   = {{Infobox name module|si|'''\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dba\u0dcf 3D'''}}}}\n\n'''''Maya''''' ({{lang-si|\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dba\u0dcf 3D}}) is a 2016 [[Sri Lanka]]n Sinhala 3D [[horror comedy film]] directed by Donald Jayantha and co-produced by Raja Sadesh Kumar and Srimathi Sadesh Kumar. It stars [[Ranjan Ramanayake]], [[Pubudu Chathuranga]] in lead roles along with [[Giriraj Kaushalya]], Nilmini Kottegoda and [[Upeksha Swarnamali]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nfc.gov.lk/films/maya-148/ | title=Maya | publisher=National Film Corporation of Sri Lanka | accessdate=24 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/11/24/?fn=sa16112430 |title=Sri Lankan Screened Films |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5961452/fullcredits?ref_=tt_ov_st_sm | title=Maya 3D (2016) | publisher=IMDB | accessdate=24 February 2017}}</ref> It is the 1257th Sri Lankan film in the [[Cinema of Sri Lanka|Sinhala cinema]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nfc.gov.lk/films-history.php | title=Sri Lanka Cinema History | publisher=National Film Corporation of Sri Lanka | accessdate=3 October 2016}}</ref> The film is based on Indian Tamil film ''[[Muni 2: Kanchana|Kanchana]]'' directed by [[Raghava Lawrence]].\n\n==Plot==\nMalan is a jobless 25 year-old youth who spends his days playing cricket with friends. He suffers from an irrational fear of ghosts and retreats to the safety of his home after sunset. His fear is so great he prefers to sleep with his widowed mother Geetha and have her accompany him to the bathroom at night, and also at the eating time. This creates major annoyance in the household, including Malan's brother Gamini, sister-in-law Nirmala  and their children.\n\nOne night, Malan engaged with a girl named Shaini and flirts to gain her attraction, but did not reveal it. Shaini also had some attraction to Malan and she started to flirt around him as well. Meanwhile, One day, Malan and his friends are forced to abandon their usual cricket ground and find a new one; one friend select an abandoned ground which is rumored to be haunted. A bizarre weather change scares them away. Malan brings home his cricket stumps, which have been stained with blood from a buried corpse in the ground. He focuses on wooing Shaini, where she asked Malan to come to a dinner. But as he is fear for ghosts, he went to the hotel with all his family. At the dinner, however, Malan's mother agreed on their relationship and fixed a date to meet Shaini's family. In the following days, his mother and sister-in-law are witness to several paranormal phenomena at night; prominently a ghost haunting the hallways. On consulting am exorcist, they perform 3 rituals to ascertain if the house is haunted:\n\n1. They keep a coconut on a [[Rangoli]] and pray with chants. The coconut rotates on its own.\n\n2. They keep an egg on a pan and see whether it turns color or explode it.\n\n3. They leave a lit lamp and two drops of blood and leave the house. A ghost of a woman appears before them and licks the blood.\n\nScared senseless, Malan's mother and sister-in-law hire two priests to rid their home of the ghost. The priests, however, are conmen, and escape with their lives. That night, the ghost possesses Malan, who begins acting increasingly [[effeminate]], alienating himself from Shaini and wearing women's clothes and jewelry. His family angrily confronts him, when it is revealed that there are actually three ghosts who have possessed him: a violent woman, a Tamil Hindu Man named Ramu, and a learning disabled boy. With the possession, Malan kills a women by hanging and a thug Wasantha by engraving him with his van. Malan's family ask Buddhist monk, who successfully drives the spirit away from Malan's body. The ghost of the woman, trapped, reveals her story.\n\nMaya/Mayantha is a [[transgender]] who was disowned by her father. She is offered shelter by a kind Tamil man Ramu, who has a [[disability]] son. Regretting that she couldn't become a doctor as she intended, she adopts another young [[transgender]] named Madhuri/Madhawi. and works hard to support her financially. When Madhuri leaves to study medicine abroad, Maya buys a plot of land where Madhuri intended to construct a hospital for the poor. That ground is unlawfully taken by Minister Ashoka. Maya angrily confronts the minister, who cunningly kills her. He also kills Ramu and his son. Before she died, she vowed to kill minister, his wife, and his henchmen Shantha. The bodies are then buried in Maya's own ground.\n\nThe Buddhist monk sympathizes with her, but remains duty-bound and traps her. After hearing her story, Malan is touched; risking the danger, he allows Maya to possess him once again. Malan/Maya confronts the minister, and disposes of his henchmen gruesomely. The minister seeks refuge in a [[Kali]] temple which Maya is forbidden from; but she asks the deity for justice and manages to chase him inside the temple. The three spirits combined kill the minister. A few years later, Malan has constructed the hospital for Dr.Madhuri as per Maya's wishes. It is revealed that Maya exists [[symbiosis|symbiotically]] in Malan's body to help him out when the need rises.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Ranjan Ramanayake]] as Maya/Mayantha\n** Yohan Perera as Young Maya/Mayantha\n* [[Pubudu Chathuranga]] as Malan\n* Shehara Hewadewa as Shaini\n* [[Giriraj Kaushalya]] as Gamini\n* Nihal Fernando as Ramu\n* Sujeewa Priyalal as Madhuri/Madhawi\n* Nilmini Kottegoda as Geetha\n* Sarath Chandrasiri as Kapuwa\n* [[Wasantha Kumaravila]] as Shantha\n* Ishan Gammudali as Buddhist monk\n* [[Somy Rathnayake]] as Principal\n* [[Upeksha Swarnamali]] as Nirmala\n* Srimal Wedisinghe as Minister Ashoka\n* [[Mihira Sirithilaka]] as Ramu's son\n* [[Kumara Thirimadura]] as Maya's father\n* [[Damitha Abeyratne]] as Shantha's fianc\u00e9e\n* Anura Bandara Rajaguru as Swami\n* [[Maureen Charuni]] as Hansi's mother\n* Ramani Siriwardena as Shaini's mother\n* Nandana Hettiarachchi as Con Priest\n* Gunadasa Madurasinghe as Con Priest\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column\t = Singer(s)\n| title1\t= Heenen Awidinna<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.topsinhalamp3.com/songs/surendra-perera-mp3-songs/heenen-awidinna-(maya)-mp3-song.php |title=Heenen Awidinna (Maya) |publisher=Top Sinhala mp3 |accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref>\n| lyrics1= Nilar N. Kasim\n| extra1 = Surendra Perera, Hirushi Jayasena\n| length1 = 2:49\n| title2\t= Maya Enawa<ref>{{cite web |url=http://livemp3music.net/mp3/Maya-Enawa-Maya-Movie-Official-Song.html |title=Maya Enawa Maya Movie Official Song mp3 Download |publisher=Live mp3 Music|accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref>\n| lyrics2= Vimalajith Dombagahawatta\n| extra2 = Uditha Sanjaya\n| length2 = 2:54\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*[http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/07/14/?fn=sa16071414 \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d86\u0dad\u0dca\u0db8 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dae\u0db8 \u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dab \u0da0\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db4\u0da7\u0dba]\n*[http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/09/08/?fn=sa16090811 \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dad\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dab\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dc0\u0dc3]\n*[http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/09/01/?fn=sa16090129 \u0db8\u0db8 \u0db8\u0ddd\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd3\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dda \u0d8b\u0dc3\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca \u0db6\u0ddd\u0dbd\u0dca\u0da7\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0da9\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dda\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca]\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt5961452}}\n* [https://www.facebook.com/Maya3DSL/ ''Maya 3D''] on [[Facebook]]\n\n[[Category:Sri Lankan films]]\n[[Category:2016 films]]\n[[Category:Sinhala-language films]]\n[[Category:Horror film remakes]]\n[[Category:Transgender-related films]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan film remakes]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Maya 3D \n| image          = File:Maya3DPoster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = Donald Jayantha\n| producer       = Raja Sadesh Kumar <br> Srimathi Sadesh Kumar\n| writer         = Raja Sadesh Kumar\n| screenplay     = Pubudu Chathuranga \n| based on       = Tamil film ''[[Kanchana (2011 film)|Kanchana]]''\n| starring       = [[Ranjan Ramanayake]] <br> [[Pubudu Chathuranga]] <br> Shehara Hewadewa\n| music          = [[Bathiya and Santhush]]\n| cinematography = Ayeshmantha Hettiarachchi\n| editing        = Pravin Jayaratne\n| studio         = Real Image Creations\n| distributor    = EAP Film Circuit\n| released       = 14 September 2016\n| runtime        = \n| country        = Sri Lanka\n| language       = Sinhalese\n| gross          = 7 LKR Crores (in 31days)\n| italic title   = \n| budget         = \n| film_name   = {{Infobox name module|si|'''\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dba\u0dcf 3D'''}}}}\n\n'''''Maya''''' ({{lang-si|\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dba\u0dcf 3D}}) is a 2016 [[Sri Lanka]]n Sinhala 3D [[horror comedy film]] directed by Donald Jayantha and co-produced by Raja Sadesh Kumar and Srimathi Sadesh Kumar. It stars [[Ranjan Ramanayake]], [[Pubudu Chathuranga]] in lead roles along with [[Giriraj Kaushalya]], Nilmini Kottegoda and [[Upeksha Swarnamali]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nfc.gov.lk/films/maya-148/ | title=Maya | publisher=National Film Corporation of Sri Lanka | accessdate=24 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/11/24/?fn=sa16112430 |title=Sri Lankan Screened Films |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5961452/fullcredits?ref_=tt_ov_st_sm | title=Maya 3D (2016) | publisher=IMDB | accessdate=24 February 2017}}</ref> It is the 1257th Sri Lankan film in the [[Cinema of Sri Lanka|Sinhala cinema]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nfc.gov.lk/films-history.php | title=Sri Lanka Cinema History | publisher=National Film Corporation of Sri Lanka | accessdate=3 October 2016}}</ref> The film is based on Indian Tamil film ''[[Muni 2: Kanchana|Kanchana]]'' directed by [[Raghava Lawrence]].\n\n==Plot==\nMalan is a jobless 25 year-old youth who spends his days playing cricket with friends. He suffers from an irrational fear of ghosts and retreats to the safety of his home after sunset. His fear is so great he prefers to sleep with his widowed mother Geetha and have her accompany him to the bathroom at night, and also at the eating time. This creates major annoyance in the household, including Malan's brother Gamini , sister-in-law Nirmala  and their children.\n\nOne night, Malan engaged with a girl named Shaini and flirts to gain her attraction, but did not reveal it. Shaini also had some attraction to Malan and she started to flirt around him as well. Meanwhile, One day, Malan and his friends are forced to abandon their usual cricket ground and find a new one; one friend select an abandoned ground which is rumored to be haunted. A bizarre weather change scares them away. Malan brings home his cricket stumps, which have been stained with blood from a buried corpse in the ground. He focuses on wooing Shaini, where she asked Malan to come to a dinner. But as he is fear for ghosts, he went to the hotel with all his family. At the dinner, however, Malan's mother agreed on their relationship and fixed a date to meet Shaini's family. In the following days, his mother and sister-in-law are witness to several paranormal phenomena at night; prominently a ghost haunting the hallways. On consulting am exorcist, they perform 3 rituals to ascertain if the house is haunted:\n\n1. They keep a coconut on a [[Rangoli]] and pray with chants. The coconut rotates on its own.\n\n2. They keep an egg on a pan and see whether it turns color or explode it.\n\n3. They leave a lit lamp and two drops of blood and leave the house. A ghost of a woman appears before them and licks the blood.\n\nScared senseless, Malan's mother and sister-in-law hire two priests to rid their home of the ghost. The priests, however, are conmen, and escape with their lives. That night, the ghost possesses Malan, who begins acting increasingly [[effeminate]], alienating himself from Shaini and wearing women's clothes and jewelry. His family angrily confronts him, when it is revealed that there are actually three ghosts who have possessed him: a violent woman, a Tamil Hindu Man named Ramu, and a learning disabled boy. With the possession, Malan kills a women by hanging and a thug Wasantha by engraving him with his van. Malan's family ask Buddhist monk, who successfully drives the spirit away from Malan's body. The ghost of the woman, trapped, reveals her story.\n\nMaya/Mayantha is a [[transgender]] who was disowned by her father. She is offered shelter by a kind Tamil man Ramu , who has a [[disability]] son. Regretting that she couldn't become a doctor as she intended, she adopts another young [[transgender]] named Madhuri/Madhawi. and works hard to support her financially. When Madhuri leaves to study medicine abroad, Maya buys a plot of land where Madhuri intended to construct a hospital for the poor. That ground is unlawfully taken by Minister Ashoka. Maya angrily confronts the minister, who cunningly kills her. He also kills Ramu and his son. Before she died, she vowed to kill minister, his wife, and his henchmen Shantha. The bodies are then buried in Maya's own ground.\n\nThe Buddhist monk sympathizes with her, but remains duty-bound and traps her. After hearing her story, Malan is touched; risking the danger, he allows Maya to possess him once again. Malan/Maya confronts the minister, and disposes of his henchmen gruesomely. The minister seeks refuge in a [[Kali]] temple which Maya is forbidden from; but she asks the deity for justice and manages to chase him inside the temple. The three spirits combined kill the minister. A few years later, Malan has constructed the hospital for Dr.Madhuri as per Maya's wishes. It is revealed that Maya exists [[symbiosis|symbiotically]] in Malan's body to help him out when the need rises.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Ranjan Ramanayake]] as Maya/Mayantha\n** Yohan Perera as Young Maya/Mayantha\n* [[Pubudu Chathuranga]] as Malan\n* Shehara Hewadewa as Shaini\n* [[Giriraj Kaushalya]] as Gamini\n* Nihal Fernando as Ramu\n* Sujeewa Priyalal as Madhuri/Madhawi\n* Nilmini Kottegoda as Geetha\n* Sarath Chandrasiri as Kapuwa\n* [[Wasantha Kumaravila]] as Shantha\n* Ishan Gammudali as Buddhist monk\n* [[Somy Rathnayake]] as Principal\n* [[Upeksha Swarnamali]] as Nirmala\n* Srimal Wedisinghe as Minister Ashoka\n* [[Mihira Sirithilaka]] as Ramu's son\n* [[Kumara Thirimadura]] as Maya's father\n* [[Damitha Abeyratne]] as Shantha's fianc\u00e9e\n* Anura Bandara Rajaguru as Swami\n* [[Maureen Charuni]] as Hansi's mother\n* Ramani Siriwardena as Shaini's mother\n* Nandana Hettiarachchi as Con Priest\n* Gunadasa Madurasinghe as Con Priest\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column\t = Singer(s)\n| title1\t= Heenen Awidinna<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.topsinhalamp3.com/songs/surendra-perera-mp3-songs/heenen-awidinna-(maya)-mp3-song.php |title=Heenen Awidinna (Maya) |publisher=Top Sinhala mp3 |accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref>\n| lyrics1= Nilar N. Kasim\n| extra1 = Surendra Perera, Hirushi Jayasena\n| length1 = 2:49\n| title2\t= Maya Enawa<ref>{{cite web |url=http://livemp3music.net/mp3/Maya-Enawa-Maya-Movie-Official-Song.html |title=Maya Enawa Maya Movie Official Song mp3 Download |publisher=Live mp3 Music|accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref>\n| lyrics2= Vimalajith Dombagahawatta\n| extra2 = Uditha Sanjaya\n| length2 = 2:54\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*[http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/07/14/?fn=sa16071414 \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d86\u0dad\u0dca\u0db8 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dae\u0db8 \u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dab \u0da0\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db4\u0da7\u0dba]\n*[http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/09/08/?fn=sa16090811 \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dad\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dab\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dc0\u0dc3]\n*[http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/09/01/?fn=sa16090129 \u0db8\u0db8 \u0db8\u0ddd\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd3\u0d9c\u0dda \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0daf\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dda \u0d8b\u0dc3\u0dda\u0db1\u0dca \u0db6\u0ddd\u0dbd\u0dca\u0da7\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0da9\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dda\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca]\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt5961452}}\n* [https://www.facebook.com/Maya3DSL/ ''Maya 3D''] on [[Facebook]]\n\n[[Category:Sri Lankan films]]\n[[Category:2016 films]]\n[[Category:Sinhala-language films]]\n[[Category:Horror film remakes]]\n[[Category:Transgender-related films]]\n[[Category:Sri Lankan film remakes]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePlot:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: ,  \u2192 ,  (2)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maya_3D"}
{"title_page": "I See Right Through to You", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = I See Right Through to You\n| cover      = DJ Encore feat. Engelina - I See Right Through To You.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[DJ Encore]] featuring [[Engelina]]\n| album      = [[Intuition (DJ Encore album)|Intuition]]\n| released   = March 2001\n| format     = [[Compact Disc single|CD single]], [[gramophone record|vinyl]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Trance music|Trance]], [[eurodance]]\n| length     = 3:49\n| label      = [[Universal Music Group|Universal]]\n| writer     = [[DJ Encore|Andreas Hemmeth]], [[Engelina]]\n| producer   = [[Michael Parsberg]], Jakob Stavnstrup, Andreas Hemmeth\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [[Walking in the Sky]]\n| next_year  = 2002\n| misc       = \n}}\n\n\"'''I See Right Through to You'''\" is a song by the [[Danish people|Danish]] [[eurodance]] [[record producer|producer]] [[DJ Encore]] featuring the vocals of Danish singer [[Engelina]]. It was released as the lead single from DJ Encore's debut album, ''[[Intuition (DJ Encore album)|Intuition]]'', in 2001. \n\nThe song served as the [[Theme music|theme song]] to the first season of the reality television show ''[[Big Brother (Denmark)|Big Brother Denmark]]''. It peaked at number one in Denmark and at number fifteen in the U.S. on [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']]'s [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] chart.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Danish CD single<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/DJ-Encore-Feat-Engelina-I-See-Right-Through-To-You/release/81737|title=DJ Encore (Feat.) Engelina \u2013 I See Right Through To You|publisher=[[discogs]]|accessdate=January 24, 2010}}</ref>\n\n| title1          = I See Right Through to You\n| note1           = Radio Edit\n| length1         = 3:49\n\n| title2          = I See Right Through to You\n| note2           =